FirstEnergy Stadium, officially FirstEnergy Stadium, Home of the Cleveland Browns and previously known as Cleveland Browns Stadium, is a multi-purpose stadium in downtown Cleveland, Ohio, United States. It is the home field of the Cleveland Browns of the National Football League, and serves as a venue for other events such as college and high school football games, soccer games, and concerts. It opened in 1999 and is located at North Coast Harbor, near the Great Lakes Science Center and the Rock and Roll Hall of Fame. The stadium sits on  of land between Lake Erie and the Cleveland Memorial Shoreway, previously the site of Cleveland Stadium from 1932â€“1996. The seating capacity is listed at 73,200 making it the 10th largest stadium in the NFL.Cleveland Browns. Accessed November 11, 2008. 